A short review from a longtime console CoD player. The game is good. No more, no less. It needs a lot of changes. Controls are clunky, the hitbox isn't consistent, and the ping isn't stable. Aiming is good for reg guns and snipers (beginners). Graphics are perfect. Hitboxes are inconsistent. The store is ridiculously stupid, lowkey P2W. Ranked is bad, it's NOT league play. Also, I'm looking forward to Zombies... BR isn't as good as I've hoped so yeah! 6/10 for now.

Maybe if I can map the button to my own liking it would be great. Hope you guys fix it! Thanks.

The multiplayer game mode is good overall, but the matching system still needs some improvement. Sometimes I encounter some unbalanced matchmaking and it really annoys me. Most of my teammates have a very low k/d ratio. Battle royale mode still needs more improvements. My frame rate constantly drops and vehicle controls aren't smooth yet. Auto login still not properly working, though, especially when i got disconnected midgame. Would rate 5/5 if the issues are fixed

The game looks really good for a mobile game, especially the level of detail on the guns and the equipments. The reason I gave it a 3 star is due to the SBMM. Screw the SBMM. Basically it puts you in match with players of equal skills instead of usually with random players. So in the sense it's harder to improve and you won't get rewarded for improving, thus making the game less and less fun. Please fix this. Please.

The graphics and gameplay is pretty rich and smooth. But the battle royale mode still requires a lot of works. That is the thing that keeps the competition. But everything else is solid. ([maybe] better than PUBG) [Edit]: How did you manage to turn it into something this lame? I'm always put into the middle (after 5-10 kills) of a match. Optimization has also become disappointing. The starting was really good but it's not the most recommended game right now.

Minus: Server is very weak compared to other games. A little higher ping will result your shots won't kill the enemies, or your character moves back in place, or worst- reconnect to the game. Random mode in multiplayer rank is unnecessary. And last thing, there will be one or two bots in team in every match, so it kills the fun. How on earth the game which has 100 million of downloads still put bots in matches? Plus: Season missions are easy to complete compared to other games.

Top of the top mobile games of all time (hopefully). The graphics looking dope, and not gonna lie the gameplay is pretty good. It's enjoyable to play with friends. This game is pretty much a mobile version of black ops, with several game modes and a battle royale. Unlike IGN's revie the touch control isnt that bad after all, but quite annoying if you're not used to it. the graphics is good for mobile but the fps can drop, depends on your internet or how capable your phone is. It's nice to be able to play a pocket size COD. There are some skins which gives advantage, but it's not necessarily pay to win.

The VTOL scorestreak is way too op, if you have that, then you can pretty much dominate the whole game. The game itself is pretty good but i gave it a 4 star. I recommend decreasing the VTOL's firing speed and duration or atleast nerf it, There is also a glitch where if you lost connection during a loading screen, it would to static and glitch all over the place

After a long waiting, its finally playable. Well, for the graphics and map obstacles is pretty good. But, yeah, for control and step sound, it's need to be improved (seriously, to be honest, it's worse than those dummies Battle Royale games). Especially on Battle Royale mode, the movement is so stiff and the step sound is only audible when the other is near you (about 10~20m, in game). However, overall is good.

I highly wholeheartedly recommend this game, but you need a high performance phone to get the best experience.

Very fun, cathartic, challenging, and faithful to the desktop/console versions of Call of Duty (particularly Black Ops). You can also partake in battle royale mode, either classic BR or Blackout-like mode. It took some getting used to the mobile controls, but as you play it, the controls become much more and more intuitive, especially after customizing the on-screen buttons. I suggest investing on separate trigger accessories to aid you. Microtransactions are very on-your-face, but all of it are cosmetics only, and don't hamper your experience playing the game for free. The season passes are one-time purchase, you can get your CP back as you grind to spend on future passes. A major inconvenience is the network/server stability; my game often stops due to the "unstable connection" even though the connection was fine and fast, both on the mobile data and wifi. The matchmaking is a little bit messy; one time my squad fought easy noobs who took forever to aim, but in the next session I get pitted with entire squad of professional operators who won the round in an instant. It's less prevalent on ranked matches but it would be nice to get constant experience on regular multiplayer matches. Overall, very good game, very fun.

I have to admit, PUBG Mobile is one of the best mobile game out there. The graphics is great, the controls are good, and gameplay is quite solid. However, it suffers from bad matchmaking, cheaters, poor performance, and a quite dull image quality. The animations is also clunky, and the worst thing is : BOTS, unnecessary events and repetitive battle passes. Overall, it's a solid, good game. But seriously, if you want to experience true battlegrounds experience, go play the PC instead. Just do it.

The game is incredible, great physics and many modes to choose from. It's content varies to simple gun game arena-type stuff to insane warfare-type stuff. It's content never runs out with a special mode coming out each month or so, although one problem It's annoying being paired up with bad players who ain't skilled at the game, then the other team is filled with pro's. What about a system which analyses the players win ratio and combat to match up with your win ratio and combat level.

PUBG has limited graphics and audio quality for Android, you need extensive wifi sometimes, and it lags every once in a while. But the game is entirely free with no ads, which is worth it. It's fun with friends and is constantly updating, but the updates take a while. Overall, it just needs a trios mode and some more weapons added. They also need to fix landing glitches in Miramar and karakin maps. There are plenty of items to choose from to clothe your avatar.

Each team member in the lobby would look cool with different weapons and different configurations.

I just end up running around most times and not really getting a chance to engage with anyone. Why not throw in the option to have them hunting all four(4) players rather than killing off each other? And why not add a couple extra tough guys (bosses) in AI MODE? Also, why not make just that portion of the game (AI MODE) playable offline?

For a free game it is solid and ad free. The game mostly runs smooth as long as you have decent internet connection. Would be nice if I could use a controller to play. Also instead of adding new content it would be nice if they cut back on some of it and just focused on the core of the game. I rolled a vehicle over the other day and couldn't get my player out resulting in death.

Could be 5*. Fun, clean, runs smooth and can be a lot of fun. They are prompt with responding to AFK/Int reports. Ranked modes have been fun and fairly balanced. Side games need work. It's good to have mini games to take in-game breaks. But they are small and heavily unbalanced. That's unavoidable without the rank system, so don't punish players for quitting an unranked mini-game. If I have an AFK and the enemy is a smurf, I don't want to feel held hostage in an unranked match.

Great game, but the lag is just unreal! The game isn't choppy or low in frames. The game tricks you into thinking it's smooth gameplay and claims that you got less than 100 ping. But you notice things like reduced damage, opponent players shooting before leaving cover, your aim and controls not working, and melee attacks hitting you even though you aren't there. I have a Galaxy A13, ~64 GB storage (half used), 4GB of ram, and 5G internet. It's fun but really frustrating because of this.

I've played the game due to its ultra graphics and adjustable game controls but this game unsatisfied me when I open it after installing it again it's login interface i.e. sign in to Facebook interrupts every time when logging in and the other issue is the occuring of bugs and lagging while in-game.

This could be SO MUCH BETTER! The game is enjoyable and very addictive. Fast paced, survival type. Graphics are ok and connecting to a server is easy. Lots of weapons to choose from and items to equip. Controlls could use a bit of tweaking. Some buttons are way too close to one another and the hud takes a lot from the actual screen. I make the mistake of firing when I don't want to when I just try to scroll around to change the view. That gets me killed often. Sometimes when the game starts, the plane goes (spawns) through the mountain. When going prone you can barely aim anywhere, so limiting. Some people spawn behind crates and are stuck there at countdown. You put too much accent on paying for better loot and character customization. The stuff you get for normal gold is simply trash compared to what you gain for using diamonds. I also get so many duplicate items. The price to spin once is ridiculous, 300 coins for a random different colored equipment that I already have. What is the actual chance of getting the cool stuff? One in a million spins?! And the most game breaking thing for me is that you are limiting the amount of coins that can be earned per day. WHY? Is it not enough that you earn just a few coins per game?? Do you have to limit us to 800 gold/day?? I am enjoying the game a lot, but if I'm to continue investing time in it, you have to make thing better for your players. Give us more maps. Make the game more accessible for those who don't want to pay in a free game and tweak the loot system. Stop limiting us.

This could be great. Graphics and control are on point. Lagged slightly. Nothing game breaking. I think it crashed once. Oh well.

Sausage Man is a good, fun, and friendly battle royale game. Some mechanics in the game are inspired by other games. But it has it's own thing that makes me want to come back and play it again and again. The game Become more fun and chaotic with friends so i'm highly recommend you to play with your friends. The issues I found is the frame rate issue which drops to 10 fps every 30 second (I'm playing in realme 6 128/4 btw). And rendering issue that very often.

This is a great and decent game. But, the sudden lag/freeze every 5 seconds is really annoying. Other people experienced this too when I read the review. Fix the ambiance sound too, for the example water/sea sound. When it stopped, it really stopped, at least make it loop so we can immerse more. On top of that, everytime the ambiance sound stopped, the game freeze again for a second. Fix this and the game will be actually playable and fun

Fun but it becomes insanely competitive once you get to Diamond (about 20 matches in). The change in difference in power of players from previous levels is abrupt and doesn't follow a smooth curve. All of a sudden, the game becomes a free for all and you are matched to the best players in every match and your win rate goes from 50% to once in a blue moon.

I guess the game is fun, but still have a lot of room for improvements. Advantages over many BRs is the game is offering fun and unique play-style, cosmetics are superb, and definitely a silly BR. The drawbacks are 1. The weapon balancing is terrible such as SMG in this game is dominating the game right now. 2. Matchmaking is not balanced at all you can be bronze and go up against master rank in your game.
